# 🧾 AI Legal Document Analyzer

An intelligent legal document analyzer built with **Python**, **Streamlit**, and **OpenRouter API**. This app allows you to upload legal documents (PDF, DOCX, or TXT), and instantly:

- 🧠 Summarize them in simple language  
- ❓ Ask questions and get answers from the content  
- 📜 View extracted text  
- 🔐 Keep your API key secure with `.env`

---

## 🚀 Demo

> Coming soon: Hosted on Streamlit Cloud  
> *(You can also run it locally — see instructions below)*

---

## 📂 Features

✅ Upload PDF, DOCX, or TXT legal files  
✅ Extracts text using PyMuPDF and `python-docx`  
✅ Summarizes documents using AI (OpenRouter API)  
✅ Ask custom questions (Q&A on document content)  
✅ Clean UI built with Streamlit  
✅ `.env` secure API key integration  
✅ Open source and easily extensible

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Python 3.10+**
- **Streamlit** – UI
- **OpenRouter API** – AI (Mistral/GPT models)
- **PyMuPDF** – PDF text extraction
- **python-docx** – DOCX handling
- **requests** – API calls
- **dotenv** – Secure environment variables

---

## 📦 Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/legal-doc-analyzer.git
cd legal-doc-analyzer


python -m venv .venv

# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate

# macOS/Linux
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt


# to run the app
streamlit run app.py


🧪 Sample Questions for Testing
"What is this agreement about?"

"Who are the involved parties?"

"When does this agreement start and end?"

"What are the confidentiality terms?"

"What happens in case of breach?"



